	<center><h1>Samsung finance</h1></center>

  <b><h2><u>INTRODUCTION</u></h2></b><br>
  <p>Finance is a field that is concerned with the allocation of assets and liabilities over space and time, often under conditions of risk or uncertainty. Finance can also be defined as the art of money management. Participants in the market aim to price assets based on their risk level, fundamental value, and their expected rate of return. Finance can be split into three sub-categories: Public, Corporate and Personal. Samsung is a multibillion dollar company competing neck to neck with many other leading electronics and construction companies. It is a South Korea based company with its headquarters in Samsung Town, Seoul. It comprises numerous affiliated businesses, most of them united under the Samsung brand. Presently it is headed by Sang hun-lee (Chairman) and Lee Jae-wong (Vice chairman), while the Finance is handles by Sun-uk Kim. </p><br>


  <b><h2><u>History</u></h2></b><br>
  <p>The company started in 1938 as an exporter of dried fish vegetables & fruits. In 1950, Due to the Korean War the country suffered a huge loss in the economy. Samsung lost all of its assets that they earned from the exporting business. To sustain in those circumstances, the company aimed at rebuilding the Korean Economy. In the process of that they entered into the manufacturing industry (Sugars, Fabrics). The company was Profit oriented since the year it was founded itself. They became leader in modern business practices and started recruiting employees from different countries which resulted in low cost. In 1960’s the company started concentrating largely on expansion. They entered in the electronics & Chemical Industries which laid the groundwork for electronics in Korea which eventually helped in Domestic Economy growth. In the 80’s they started to export their goods globally which helped in gaining reputation globally and also led them to increase their profits exponentially. To cut down the transportation costs and to get cheaper labour they established plants in Portugal & United States. They also entered into Semiconductor & Communication Corporation. In the next decade the company wholly concentrated on Integration & Globalization. They also implemented new management strategies according to the Employees, Market and Customers that they gained due to global expansion. Their core markets included home, mobile, personal multimedia. <br>
In 1996, the company suffered hugely in their Revenue growth & operating income. This made the company to change their CEO and give a chance to others. Here comes Jong Yong Yun. He made revolutionary changes in the company. 
</p><br>
