<b><h2><u>CURRENT SCENARIO</u></h2></b><br>
  <p>Samsung is presently placed 2nd in the Forbes list in the list of largest Tech based companies (only below Apple) and 14th largest company overall in the world. It now has a huge worldwide network of electronics and other subsidiaries like Engineering, C&T Corporation, Heavy industries, Life insurance, all coming under the brand SAMSUNG. The company has also come up with SAMSUNG NEXT which specifically focuses on present day start-ups and has already invested multimillion dollars in them by now globally. This resulted in stakes of up to 29.9% in 80+ start-ups. They also contributed to the company’s profits along with the subsidiaries.  It saw $225 billion in sales, $21 billion in profit, $293 billion in assets and a market cap of $326 billion. </p><br>

